The paper discusses multi-task learning in deep neural networks, which is a topic that spans several sub-categories of computer science. However, given the focus on deep learning and neural networks, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses applications in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV), which suggest cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses recent advances in MTL, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
